This paper belongs to the sub-category of AI called Case Based. 

Explanation: 
The title of the paper, "CBET: a Case Base Exploration Tool," suggests that the focus of the paper is on case-based reasoning. The abstract also mentions that the tool is designed to "support the exploration of case bases," further emphasizing the case-based approach. The paper describes how the CBET tool uses case-based reasoning to help users explore and analyze large case bases. The other sub-categories of AI (Genetic Algorithms, Neural Networks, Probabilistic Methods, Reinforcement Learning, Rule Learning, Theory) are not mentioned in the text and are therefore not applicable.
